benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Deletion Coverage: Deletions succeed across multiple test cases (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC17, TC18).
Non-Existent Resource Coverage: 404 responses for nonexistent account (TC03), missing email (TC04), and account with no emails (TC09).
Input Validation Coverage: 400 responses for invalid accountId (TC05), invalid email (TC06), missing required header (TC07), and XSS/injection attempt in email parameter (TC16).
Authorization Coverage: 401 on invalid/expired authentication token (TC10).
System/Dependency/Resilience Coverage: 503 when email service unavailable (TC11).
Performance Coverage: Deletion response time under 500ms (TC14).
Query Parameter Handling Coverage: Supports extra, unsupported query parameter without breaking deletion (TC08).
Boundary Data Coverage: Very long email address (TC12) and minimal-length email (TC13).
Regression Coverage: Case-insensitive deletion (TC17) and backward compatibility with legacy API clients (TC18).
Concurrency Coverage: 5 concurrent deletions for the same email; one 204 and rest 404 (TC15).
Security/Invalid Input Coverage: Deleting with XSS injection is rejected (TC16).
Recovery/Retry Coverage: Deletion may succeed after transient failure with a retry (TC19).
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit soft-delete semantics tested for this endpoint.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses.
403 Forbidden: Only 401 Unauthorized is tested; no test for insufficient privileges (403).
Observability/Logging: No tests verifying logs or metrics for delete operations.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges during deletion.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure proper handling under high request load.
Add tests to validate caching headers and behaviors for DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control).
Add soft-delete semantics validation to confirm whether deletions are physical or logical.
Add tests for header value validation beyond presence (e.g., format of X-Killbill-CreatedBy, Reason, Comment).
Introduce tests to validate observability (logs/metrics) during delete operations.
